# Project Rules

## Tech Stack

- **Orchestration**: Kubernetes (k3d/k3s for local, targeting single-node demo environment)
- **GitOps**: Argo CD — this repo IS the source of truth for all deployed state
- **Secret Management**: HashiCorp Vault + External Secrets Operator (ESO)
- **Message Queue**: RabbitMQ (deployed, Stages 1-4 complete)
- **Databases**: PostgreSQL StatefulSets (products, orders) + Redis StatefulSets (cart, orders-cache)
- **Identity**: Keycloak + OpenLDAP in `identity` namespace
- **Helm**: Used for application service charts (`chart/` directory)
- **Kustomize**: Used for service `k8s/base/` directories in application repos
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions (PR validation) → Jenkins (build/push) → this repo (Helm values update) → Argo CD (sync)
- **Container Registry**: GHCR (ghcr.io) for production; local k3s image import for development
- **Image Build**: Podman (not Docker) for local builds

## Architecture

Two-namespace model:
- `shopping-cart-data` — StatefulSets (PostgreSQL, Redis, RabbitMQ), PVCs, ExternalSecrets
- `shopping-cart-apps` — Application Deployments (frontend, product-catalog, basket, order), Services
- `identity` — Keycloak + OpenLDAP
- `argocd` — Argo CD itself
- `vault` — HashiCorp Vault
- `monitoring` — Prometheus stack (from observability-stack repo)

```
shopping-cart-infra/
├── data-layer/         # PostgreSQL + Redis StatefulSets + ExternalSecrets
├── argocd/
│   ├── projects/       # AppProject definition (shopping-cart)
│   └── applications/   # ArgoCD Application CRDs (basket, order, product-catalog, apps)
├── identity/
│   ├── keycloak/       # Keycloak Deployment + PostgreSQL + ConfigMap + Secret
│   └── ldap/           # OpenLDAP Deployment + bootstrap config
├── namespaces/         # Namespace definitions
├── vault/              # Vault database secrets engine setup script
├── chart/              # Helm chart for application services (app-level deployments)
├── bin/                # Operational scripts
├── docs/               # Documentation
├── examples/           # Dockerfile templates + GitHub Actions templates
└── jenkins/            # Jenkinsfile.update-image
```

## Code Conventions

### YAML Formatting
- 2-space indentation throughout
- All Kubernetes resources must have both `app` and `app.kubernetes.io/name` labels
- Use `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: shopping-cart` for Argo CD application labeling
- Include namespace in every resource metadata block
- Add `finalizers: [resources-finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io]` to all Argo CD Application resources

### Kubernetes Manifests
- Never hardcode secrets — all secrets come from ExternalSecrets (Vault) or are templated
- StatefulSets must have `serviceName` matching a Headless Service
- Argo CD Applications: always set `syncPolicy.automated.prune: true` and `selfHeal: true`
- Image tags in Helm values must be updated by CI (Jenkins) — never commit `latest` in values files
- Resource limits must always be specified; see demo environment targets below

### Demo Environment Resource Limits (8GB single-node k3s)
| Component | CPU Request | Memory Request | CPU Limit | Memory Limit |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| PostgreSQL | 100m | 256Mi | 500m | 512Mi |
| Redis | 50m | 128Mi | 200m | 256Mi |
| RabbitMQ | 100m | 256Mi | 500m | 512Mi |
| Application pods | 50m | 64Mi | 200m | 256Mi |
| Prometheus | 100m | 256Mi | 250m | 512Mi |

### Security
- Never commit secrets, passwords, or tokens to this repository
- All credentials managed via Vault + ESO
- Redis passwords: Vault KV at `secret/redis/cart` and `secret/redis/orders`
- PostgreSQL credentials: Vault Database Secrets Engine (dynamic, 1h TTL)
- Use `vault kv put` for static secrets; never `kubectl create secret` with literal passwords

### Conventional Commits
Use these prefixes for commit messages:
- `infra:` — infrastructure changes (manifests, StatefulSets)
- `feat:` — new infrastructure components
- `fix:` — bug fixes in manifests or scripts
- `chore:` — image tag updates, routine maintenance
- `docs:` — documentation updates

## Testing

### Validating Kubernetes Manifests
```bash
# Dry-run apply to validate YAML syntax and schema
kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f <manifest>

# Validate Helm chart
helm lint chart/
helm template test chart/ -f chart/values.yaml --debug

# Validate kustomize
kubectl kustomize k8s/base/
```

### Checking Deployment Health
```bash
make status              # Overall cluster status
make rabbitmq-status     # RabbitMQ cluster status
make vault-status        # Vault seal status
make argocd-status       # ArgoCD pod status
kubectl get pods -n shopping-cart-data
kubectl get pods -n shopping-cart-apps
kubectl get externalsecrets -n shopping-cart-data  # ESO sync status
```

### Load Testing RabbitMQ
```bash
make load-test-quick       # 50 msgs/sec for 5s
make load-test-burst       # 1000 msgs/sec for 30s
make load-test-sustained   # 100 msgs/sec for 10min
make load-test-alert       # Trigger Prometheus alerts
```

## Build & Run

### Deploying Infrastructure from Scratch
```bash
# 1. Create namespaces
kubectl apply -f namespaces/namespaces.yaml

# 2. Configure Vault (run after Vault is initialized and unsealed)
./vault/setup-database-secrets-engine.sh

# 3. Deploy data layer
kubectl apply -f data-layer/postgresql/products/
kubectl apply -f data-layer/postgresql/orders/
kubectl apply -f data-layer/redis/cart/
kubectl apply -f data-layer/redis/orders-cache/
kubectl apply -f data-layer/secrets/

# 4. Deploy Argo CD applications
kubectl apply -f argocd/projects/
kubectl apply -f argocd/applications/

# 5. Deploy identity stack
kubectl apply -k identity/ldap/
kubectl apply -k identity/keycloak/

# Or use make targets:
make argocd-deploy
make identity-deploy
```

### Building and Importing Container Images (local k3s)
```bash
make images-build   # Build with podman
make images-save    # Save to /tmp/*.tar
make images-import  # Import into k3s (requires sudo)
```

### CI/CD Image Update Flow
Jenkins reads `INFRA_REPO` and runs:
```bash
yq eval ".<service>.image.tag = '<git-sha>'" -i chart/values-dev.yaml
git commit -m "chore: update <service> to <git-sha>"
git push origin main
# Argo CD detects change and syncs within 3 minutes (or via webhook)
```

### Useful Make Targets
```bash
make help               # Full target list
make status             # K8s + RabbitMQ status
make rabbitmq-ui        # Port-forward to RabbitMQ management (localhost:15672)
make grafana            # Port-forward to Grafana (localhost:3000)
make prometheus         # Port-forward to Prometheus (localhost:9090)
make vault-ui           # Port-forward to Vault UI (localhost:8200)
make argocd-ui          # Port-forward to ArgoCD UI (localhost:8080)
make keycloak-ui        # Port-forward to Keycloak UI (localhost:8080)
make db-orders-shell    # psql into orders database
make db-products-shell  # psql into products database
make debug-vault-unseal # Unseal Vault using stored key
make debug-events       # Show recent K8s events
```

## Key Patterns

### Vault ExternalSecret Pattern
```yaml
apiVersion: external-secrets.io/v1beta1
kind: ExternalSecret
metadata:
  name: <secret-name>
  namespace: shopping-cart-data
spec:
  refreshInterval: 1h
  secretStoreRef:
    name: vault-backend
    kind: SecretStore
  target:
    name: <k8s-secret-name>
  data:
    - secretKey: username
      remoteRef:
        key: database/creds/<role>
        property: username
    - secretKey: password
      remoteRef:
        key: database/creds/<role>
        property: password
```

### Argo CD Application Pattern
```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: <service-name>
  namespace: argocd
  finalizers: [resources-finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io]
spec:
  project: shopping-cart
  source:
    repoURL: https://github.com/your-org/<service-repo>.git
    targetRevision: HEAD
    path: k8s/base
  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
    namespace: shopping-cart-apps
  syncPolicy:
    automated: { prune: true, selfHeal: true, allowEmpty: false }
    syncOptions: [CreateNamespace=true, PrunePropagationPolicy=foreground]
    retry: { limit: 5, backoff: { duration: 5s, factor: 2, maxDuration: 3m } }
  ignoreDifferences:
    - group: apps
      kind: Deployment
      jsonPointers: [/spec/replicas]  # Ignore HPA-managed replicas
```

### RabbitMQ Message Schema Pattern
All messages use a common envelope:
```json
{
  "id": "uuid-v4",
  "type": "order.created",
  "version": "1.0",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601",
  "source": "order-service",
  "correlationId": "uuid-v4",
  "data": { ... }
}
```
Exchanges: `events` (topic), `commands` (direct), `dlx` (fanout for dead letters).
Routing key convention: `<domain>.<event>.<optional-qualifier>`.
